      "id": "c1799525_212594f8",
      "file_path": "cps-ncmp-rest-stub/cps-ncmp-rest-stub-service/src/test/groovy/org/onap/cps/ncmp/rest/stub/providers/ResourceProviderSpec.groovy",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": null,
      "message": "Overall good test but I can see you are new to groovy/Spock so hence some general notes and tips on Groovy:\n- don't use \" for strings but always ' (\" is used for GroovyStrings , they are like macros(Google Groovy String) \n(for convenience if your data has ' inside the string you can still use \" ) eg. def title = \"John's book\"\n- remove all ; \n- no type or java modifiers (except for static')\n- for more see https://wiki.onap.org/pages/viewpage.action?pageId=92998161",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 6639,
        "name": "Toine Siebelink",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "toine.siebelink@est.tech",
        "username": "ToineSiebelink"
      },
      "updated": "2023-06-21 14:32:39.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "16f5434f_15f7a8b6",
      "file_path": "cps-ncmp-rest-stub/cps-ncmp-rest-stub-service/src/test/groovy/org/onap/cps/ncmp/rest/stub/providers/ResourceProviderSpec.groovy",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 32,
      "message": "prefer to use untyped in Groofy ie. 'def'",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 6639,
