    },
    {
      "id": "93379bd6_c290e269",
      "file_path": "cps-ncmp-rest-stub/cps-ncmp-rest-stub-service/src/test/groovy/org/onap/cps/ncmp/rest/stub/providers/ResourceProviderSpec.groovy",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 44,
      "message": "don't use term like 'should' or expectation in the test description (that is what the labels in Spock are for) instead use short 'scenarios'\n\n'Resource Provider with existing file'",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 6639,
        "name": "Toine Siebelink",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "toine.siebelink@est.tech",
        "username": "ToineSiebelink"
      },
      "updated": "2023-06-21 14:32:39.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "bf313efc_9bf58a80",
      "file_path": "cps-ncmp-rest-stub/cps-ncmp-rest-stub-service/src/test/groovy/org/onap/cps/ncmp/rest/stub/providers/ResourceProviderSpec.groovy",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 46,
      "message": "I am not a big fan of 'additional' blank lines, they can be useful to separate large blocka (although it might really be a code smell for refactoring then)  . Its not a blockign issue I dint think anyone in the team does so I prefer if you remove them too",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 6639,
        "name": "Toine Siebelink",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "toine.siebelink@est.tech",
        "username": "ToineSiebelink"
      },
      "updated": "2023-06-21 14:32:39.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "82604d8b_259cd859",
      "file_path": "cps-ncmp-rest-stub/cps-ncmp-rest-stub-service/src/test/groovy/org/onap/cps/ncmp/rest/stub/providers/ResourceProviderSpec.groovy",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 46,
      "message": "please provide a short 'description' after each label. The idea is that teh combination of given, when then and thos descriptions reads as a single sentence that someone not so familiar with teh coding language can understand I often call it 'ProductOwnner-Speak' Therefore we also try to avoid exact classnames but instead you short word that a clear enough in the scope of the test \n\nin your case something like\n\ngiven 'a resource provider for a temporary folder'\nand 'a file in that temporary folder'\nwhen 'attempting to access that file'#\nthen 'it is present'",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 6639,
        "name": "Toine Siebelink",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "toine.siebelink@est.tech",
        "username": "ToineSiebelink"
      },
      "updated": "2023-06-21 14:32:39.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
    },
